text: The Baojun 560 is a compact Crossover SUV made by SAIC-GM-Wuling under Baojun from 2015 to 2018. == History and Features == The Baojun 560 was launched in the Chinese market in 2015. the car has a 1.5 liter turbo Daewoo petrol engine (launched in 2017) and a 1.8 liter turbo petrol engine with a 5 and 6-speed manual transmissions a 5-speed semi-automatic transmission and a 6-speed DCT transmission. == Markets == The Baojun 560 was sold mainly in the Chinese market during its entire production. == Discontinuation == The production of The 560 ended in 2018 and was later replaced by the Baojun 530. == References == Category:Chinese automobiles Category:2010s automobiles Category:Sport utility vehicles
